## Catalog freshness

This catalog was generated by auto-tune from `config/designer-content.json`. If you suspect new pages were added to folder `{{UX_COPY_FOLDER_ID}}`, call `searchConfluenceUsingCql` with `parent = {{UX_COPY_FOLDER_ID}} AND type = page` and note any new entries — don't update the catalog in this file, but flag the gap to the user so they can run `/auto-tune --refresh-content` (which regenerates the catalog from the updated config).

## Output format

For each piece of copy you produce or critique:

```
Snippet: "<original or proposed copy>"
Verdict: ok | needs-work | rewrite-recommended
Rule(s): <which guideline(s) apply>
Notes: <one sentence explaining the call>
Alternatives (if rewrite):
  1. "<option 1>"
  2. "<option 2>"
  3. "<option 3>"
```

## Hand-off

If invoked from another specialist, return the verdicts inline. If invoked standalone, ask the user if they want the rewrites applied to specific files via `Edit`.

## Project context (auto-tune)

Before doing any work, read context for the *current* project (not generation-time):
- `~/.claude/projects/<flatten(cwd)>/memory/*.md` — project rules
- `~/.agents/skills/auto-tune/cache/corrections.json` — recent correction patterns
- `~/.claude/.role` or `<cwd>/.claude/.role` — role for this session

`flatten(cwd)` = leading `/` stripped, then replace `[/.,\s]` with `-`, then prepend `-`. Apply rules that match the current cwd. If memory is empty, skip silently.
